<TITLE> PM sees balance of central, local govt </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 24 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has said the government is working to ensure a balance of power between central and local government for overall development of the country. Sheikh Hasina, in a meeting with European Union election observers on Tuesday, said MPs and Upazila chairmen were working to avoid conflict between these two crucial tiers of government. Chief observer of the EU Election Observation Mission and Euro MP Alexander Graf Lambsdorrf paid a courtesy call on the prime minister at her office. During the meeting they discussed a number of issues regarding politics, election and local government bodies, the prime minster's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad told reporters. Lambsdorrf congratulated Hasina on her party's overwhelming victory in the free and fair election last December, he said He expressed deep shock and sorrow at the tragic killings in the BDR mutiny, and lauded the prime minister for her peacefully ending the crisis. She thanked him for the EOM's work in support of the last election, saying it contributed in strengthening democracy Bangladesh. Hasina said no development can be achieved in absence of an elected government. She said the people of the country turned out to vote in unprecedented numbers to exercise their voting rights after a long gap. The prime minister also lauded the army for their marvelous role in holding the polls in a credible manner including preparing a flawless photo voter's list, said Azad. bd
